In [MainClientExec][1], all the return values from execute look like:

    return new HttpResponseProxy(response, connHolder);

where connHolder can be null.

[HttpResponseProxy][2] is just a thin wrapper that does a close on the connHolder. Unfortunately, it is package protected, so it&#39;s not (necessarily) visible.

What I did was create a &quot;PublicHttpResponseProxy&quot;

    package org.apache.http.impl.execchain;

    import org.apache.http.HttpResponse;

    public class PublicHttpResponseProxy extends HttpResponseProxy {

        public PublicHttpResponseProxy(HttpResponse original) {
            super(original, null);
        }
    }

