Spring has a nice Utility class [`ReflectionUtils`][1] that does just that: it defines a method to loop over all fields of all super classes with a callback: [`ReflectionUtils.doWithFields()`][2]

Documentation:
--------------

&gt; Invoke the given callback on all fields in the target class,
&gt; going up the class hierarchy to get all declared fields.

&gt; **Parameters:**  
&gt; -        clazz - the target class to analyze   
&gt; -        fc - the callback to invoke for each field  
&gt; -        ff - the filter that determines the fields to apply the callback to   


